EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on United States corporate sponsors of the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics with headquarters and operations in New York City to meaningfully engage the Chinese government in proactively addressing their role in the ongoing crisis in Darfur and to withdraw from and withhold any commitment to support the Olympics if the Chinese government fails to sever its financial connections with Sudan or to leverage its connections to hold Sudan accountable for ending the genocide in Darfur before December 31, 2007.
EventItemMatterName: Calling on US corporate sponsors of the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics with headquarters and operations in NYC to meaningfully engage the Chinese government in proactively addressing their role in the ongoing crisis in Darfur.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of City Planning to promulgate rules to ensure that no new residential developments shall be certified unless and until the Department of City Planning certifies the presence or projected presence of sufficient open space for the neighborhood’s current and projected residential and commercial population.
EventItemMatterName: City Planning to promulgate rules to ensure that no new residential developments shall be certified.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of City Planning to promulgate rules to ensure that no new residential developments shall be certified unless and until the Department of City Planning certifies the presence or projected presence of sufficient school space for the neighborhood’s current and projected population of school age children.
EventItemMatterName: City Planning to promulgate rules to ensure that no new residential developments shall be certified.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of City Planning to propose a text amendment to the zoning resolution, creating a new Use Group governing Telecom Hotels, mandating that Telecom Hotels never be located in commercial, residential or special mixed use districts.
EventItemMatterName: Department of City Planning to propose a text amendment to the zoning resolution, creating a new Use Group governing Telecom Hotels.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of City Planning to regulate the special manufacturing districts of NoHo, SoHo and Tribeca as residential use districts with respect to billboards and signage and not as manufacturing use districts.
EventItemMatterName: City Planning to regulate the special manufacturing districts of NoHo, SoHo and Tribeca as residential use districts.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring reports to the city council of any variance or special permit granted when the community board recommended disapproval or approval with conditions.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring reports to the city council of any variance or special permit granted when the community board recommended disapproval or approval with conditions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Board of Elections to promptly commission the development of a Precinct Based Optical Scan voting system that would comply with New York State voting system standards, which would be owned entirely by the State of New York and would be certified for use by the county Boards of Elections and by the Board of Elections in the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Board of Elections to promptly commission the development of a Precinct Based Optical Scan voting system that would comply with New York State voting system standards.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for a symbolic moratorium on pejorative use of the “b” word and the word “ho.”
EventItemMatterName: Calling for a symbolic moratorium on pejorative use of the “b” word and the word “ho”.

EventItemMatterName: Establishing a New York City Municipal Identification Card.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution denouncing the use by President Bush and Homeland Security Secretary Chertoff of a flawed risk-based allotment of anti-terrorism grants and failing to recognize that New York City is one of the top targets for an international terrorist attack, and calling on President Bush and Homeland Security Secretary Chertoff to increase homeland security funding for New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Denouncing the use by President Bush and Homeland Security Secretary Chertoff of a flawed risk-based allotment of anti-terrorism grants.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and adopt, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would amend the New York State Real Property Tax Law (RPTL) to expand the veterans’ property tax exemption to include an exemption on the school portion of the tax for veterans with incomes below $47,500 and to increase the maximum income eligibility thresholds of the Senior Citizen Homeowners Exemption (SCHE) program and the Disabled Homeowners Exemption (DHE) program to the same level.
